      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Add chopped garlic and sliced chilies to the hot oil and stir-fry briefly until fragrant and just beginning to color (about 20-30 seconds), taking care not to burn the garlic.",
        "time_min": 1
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Increase heat to high, add ground chicken, breaking it up with a spatula. Stir-fry until mostly cooked through and just starting to brown, about 4-5 minutes.",
        "time_min": 5
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "Push the meat to the side and add sliced shallot; stir for about 30 seconds then mix everything together.",
        "time_min": 1
      },
      {
        "step_no": 6,
        "text": "Add soy sauce, oyster sauce, fish sauce, sugar, and white pepper. Stir continuously to coat the chicken and let the sauce reduce slightly, about 1-2 minutes.",
        "time_min": 2
      },
      {
        "step_no": 7,
        "text": "Taste and adjust seasoning (add a little more fish sauce or sugar as preferred). Turn off the heat and fold in the basil leaves until wilted from residual heat, about 30 seconds.",
        "time_min": 1
      },
      {
        "step_no": 8,
        "text": "In a separate small skillet, heat a little oil over medium-high heat and fry eggs sunny-side up with crispy edges if desired (one per serving).",
        "time_min": 4
      },
      {
        "step_no": 9,
        "text": "Serve the basil chicken over steamed rice, top each bowl with a fried egg if using, and garnish with lime wedges. Serve immediately.",
